# sdkconfig.project — project-level ESP-IDF overrides
#
# This file is Layer 1 of a 3-tier workaround to reduce FATFS/WL sector sizes
# from 4096 to 512 (saving ~18KB heap during SD mount). For full context, see
# platformio.ini and docs/archive/56-POST-IMP-G31A.md.
#
# We use this external file referenced via "file://sdkconfig.project" in the
# custom_sdkconfig block because PlatformIO's INI parser silently strips
# "# CONFIG_X is not set" lines as comments, but the builder reads file:// raw.
#
# ── FATFS / Wear-Levelling Sector Size ──
# Override the default 4096-byte sector to 512-byte.
# This reduces contiguous heap consumed by FATFS.win[] and FIL.buf[]
# during SD card mount: each buffer shrinks from 4096 → 512 bytes.
# Without these overrides, SD_MMC.begin() drops max_alloc by ~18KB.
#
# IMPORTANT: Both the Kconfig boolean selectors (_4096/_512) and the
# raw value (CONFIG_WL_SECTOR_SIZE) must be set. The base Arduino
# sdkconfig has _4096=y; without explicitly unsetting it, the ESP-IDF
# build system ignores the raw value override.
# CONFIG_WL_SECTOR_SIZE_4096 is not set
CONFIG_WL_SECTOR_SIZE_512=y
CONFIG_WL_SECTOR_SIZE=512
# CONFIG_FATFS_SECTOR_4096 is not set
CONFIG_FATFS_SECTOR_512=y
